results.name: a(1)=5. For n > 1, a(n) = 4*5^(n-1) = A005054(n).
comment: a(n) is the total number of holes in all nonnegative n-digit integers. For example, 0, 6 and 9 have 1 hole, while 8 has 2 holes. That adds up to a total of 5 for 1-digit integers. - _Tanya Khovanova_, Sep 18 2007
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
formula: O.g.f.: 5*x*(1-x)/(1-5*x). - Better definition from _R. J. Mathar_, May 13 2008
mathematica: Rest[CoefficientList[Series[5 x (1 - x)/(1 - 5 x), {x,0,50}], x]] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Sep 01 2017 *)
